(1337, '978-617-07-0576-1', '“Just David” is one more novel by a world-famous American writer Eleanor H. Porter (1868—1920), the author of the best-seller about Pollyanna. Unlike “Pollyanna”, a charming tale about the girl, “Just David” is not less moving and interesting story about the unusual boy with crystal-clear soul, who so splendidly masters the art of playing violin that even the most hard-hearted and insensible people, listening to his music and communicating with him, become more kind-hearted and begin to see beauty around them.', 8, '773', 843, 'https://img.yakaboo.ua/media/catalog/product/cache/1/image/200x300/234c7c011ba026e66d29567e1be1d1f7/i/m/img406_1_20.jpg', 'Just David', 75, 'Элинор Портер', '', 'Офсетная', '169 гр.', '', '2018', '', '', 'Знання', '', 'Нет иллюстраций', '', '', '222', '', '', 'Литература XIX - нач. XX в. (до 1918 г.)', 'Литература США и Канады', '', '', 'Твердый', '', '', '', '', 'American Library', '', '', 'Бумажная', '', '110х170 мм', '', 'Английский'),
